  "prompt": "What is Cisco 2.0?",
  "response": "Cisco 2.0 refers to Cisco Systems' strategic approach to evolving its business model and technology offerings in response to changing market dynamics and technological advancements. It typically involves:\n\n1. Cloud-based solutions\n2. Software-defined networking (SDN)\n3. Enhanced digital transformation services\n4. Greater focus on subscription and recurring revenue models\n5. More flexible and agile technology architectures\n6. Increased emphasis on cybersecurity\n7. Integration of artificial intelligence and machine learning\n8. Modernizing network infrastructure\n\nThe \"2.0\" concept suggests a modernized, more adaptive approach to networking and technology services compared to Cisco's traditional hardware-centric model.",
